islVlanMIB.name: islVlanMIB
islVlanMIB.contactinfo: NetMetrix Division Hewlett-Packard Company 5070 Centennial Blvd Colorado Springs, CO 80919
islVlanMIB.description: The MIB module to configure Cisco ISL VLAN monitoring.

islVlanControlTable.name: islVlanControlTable
islVlanControlTable.description: A list ISL VLAN control entries, one for each 100BaseT interface. This table should survive warm-boots and power losses.

islVlanControlEntry.name: islVlanControlEntry
islVlanControlEntry.description: An entry that controls the ISL behavior on a particular 100BaseT interface.

islVlanControlIndex.name: islVlanControlIndex
islVlanControlIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies this islVlanControlTable entry.

islVlanControlDataSource.name: islVlanControlDataSource
islVlanControlDataSource.description: This contains the OID of the ifIndex of the interface this entry controls. The corresponding ifType ethernetCsmacd(6).

islVlanControlVtpDomain.name: islVlanControlVtpDomain
islVlanControlVtpDomain.description: The IP address of the Cisco VTP server of VLANs monitored by this interface.

islVlanControlVtpCommunity.name: islVlanControlVtpCommunity
islVlanControlVtpCommunity.description: The SNMP community string for the Cisco VTP server of VLANs monitored by this interface.

islVlanControlEnable.name: islVlanControlEnable
islVlanControlEnable.description: Indicate the behavior for processing ISL VLAN packets. A value of disabled(1) means that no per-VLAN monitoring happens on this interface. A value of explicitlyOnly(2) means that only VLANs that correspond to an islVlanEntry that was explicitly created by a management application. If the probe sees an ISL packet that doesn't correspond to an explicitly created islVlanEntry, the probe will not process the packet in any per-VLAN tables. A value of implicitCreate(3) means that a new islVlanEntry is automatically created when a ISL packet is seen with an unknown VLAN ID.

islVlanTable.name: islVlanTable
islVlanTable.description: The ISL VLAN able stores the information needed to monitor Cisco ISL VLAN traffic on an inter-switch trunk line. This table should survive warm-boots and power losses.

islVlanEntry.name: islVlanEntry
islVlanEntry.description: An entry in the islVlanTable. An entry can be created two ways. A management application can explicitly create an entry. Or, an entry can be automatically created if an unknown ISL ID is seen on an interface (see islVlanControlEnable.)

islVlanIndex.name: islVlanIndex
islVlanIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies this islVlanTable entry.

islVlanControlEntryIndex.name: islVlanControlEntryIndex
islVlanControlEntryIndex.description: Indicates the islVlanControlIndex of the corresponding islVlanControlEntry.

islVlanId.name: islVlanId
islVlanId.description: The value of this object ISL VLAN ID for this particular VLAN on this interface.

islVlanIfIndex.name: islVlanIfIndex
islVlanIfIndex.description: A unique identifier associated with this islVlanTable entry. This value should not be same as any existing or future ifIndex/pvcIndex value. This value must remain constant from when its creation until its explicit deletion.

islVlanName.name: islVlanName
islVlanName.description: This contains the VLAN name. If the entry was created automatically by the probe, its value is `unknown VLAN <ID>'. A management application is free to change this name at any time.

islVlanMtu.name: islVlanMtu
islVlanMtu.description: The maximum transmission unit size for this VLAN. If this was created automatically, this value not be known and should be set to 0.

islVlanOwner.name: islVlanOwner
islVlanOwner.description: The entity that configured this entry. If this was automatically created by the probe, the value is `monitor'.

islVlanStatus.name: islVlanStatus
islVlanStatus.description: The status of this islVlanTable entry.
